  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Patients suffering from sudden worsening of congestive heart failure, who are examined at
        the Emergency department or admitted to University Hospital
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  able to provide informed consent

          -  aged 19 years or more

          -  history of heart failure of at least one month

          -  examined or hospitalized for acute dyspnea at rest or with minimal exertion

          -  clinical signs of fluid overload defined as at least one of following:

          -  rales

          -  jugular venous distension

          -  peripheral edema

          -  pulmonary congestion on X-ray

          -  NT-proBNP above 210 pmo/l

        Exclusion Criteria:
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
